line_1: Between the German and the Turk:
line_2: Tokay and Coffee cause this Work,

line_1: THUS says the prophet of the Turk,
My Faith was sixt, I always was a Turk;
line_2: In vain did English Education work,

line_1: And balk'd both Pagan, and the Christian Turk,
line_2: Lent th' golden Mattock to this pious work,

line_1: And balk'd both Pagan, and the Christian Turk,
line_2: Who slily did like snarling Blood-hound lurk,

line_1: Troth Sir, you have less Conscience than a Turk,
line_2: To put an honest Muse on Conjuring Work,

line_1: Troth Sir, you have less Conscience than a Turk,
line_2: To make Wesphalia Hams of English Pork.

line_1: Like Bow-string sent from the Grand Turk.
